%p
  Hello #{@teacher.name},
%p
  We noticed that you haven't logged in to your Code.org account in over 3 years. To keep our systems secure and up-to-date, we regularly delete accounts that have been inactive.
%h3
  What's happening?
%p
  Your account is scheduled for deletion in 30 days due to 3 years of inactivity on the Code.org platform.
%h3
  How to keep your account:
%p
  If you'd like to keep your Code.org account active, simply log back in at any time within the next 30 days. This will automatically prevent your account from being deleted.
%h3
  What if you miss the 30-day deadline?
%p
  If your account has already been deleted after 30 days, you can still contact Code.org Support to attempt to recover your account—but only for a limited time of 28 days after deletion. After that period, your account and all associated personal data on the Code.org platform will be permanently deleted and cannot be recovered.
  If you have any questions or need help, please reply to this email or reach out to
  %a{href:SharedConstants::EMAIL_LINKS.CDO_SUPPORT_MAILTO}support@code.org.
%p
  Thank you,
%p
  The Code.org Team
